                <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Report by the Deputies</hi>
                </p>
                <p>This Report was submitted by the Chairman in office and adopted.</p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Draft Peace Treaty With Italy</hi>: <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 177<note n="53" xml:id="d182fn53">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Restitution</hi> (Appendix II<note n="54" xml:id="d182fn54">Appendix II is printed separately as <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 138, June 5, 1946, <ref target="#pg_470">p. 470</ref>.</note>)</p>
                <p>In the text proposed in paragraph 1 of Part II the Council agreed to insert after
                    the words “by force” the words “or duress” as proposed in sub-paragraph (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>).</p>
                <p>Paragraph 1 of Part III, dealing with the burden of proof, was referred back to
                    the Economic Experts for study.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Economic and Financial Provisions
                        Relating to Ceded Territories</hi> (Appendix VI)<note n="55" xml:id="d182fn55">Appendix VI is printed separately as <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 153, June 11, 1946, <ref target="#pg_481">p. 481</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Part I of this Appendix was adopted, subject to the reservations specified
                    therein.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">IV. <hi rend="italic">General Economic Clauses</hi> (Appendix
                        IV)<note n="56" xml:id="d182fn56">Appendix IV is printed separately as
                            <gloss target="#t_CFMD461">C.F.M.(D) (46)</gloss> 167, June 12, 1946,
                            <ref target="#pg_488">p. 488</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Council discussed Part II of this Appendix. No agreement was reached.</p>
                <pb facs="0569" n="547" xml:id="pg_547"/>
                <p rend="flushleft">V. <hi rend="italic">Personal Injuries</hi> (Art. 66)</p>
                <p>To be discussed later by the Council of Foreign Ministers.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">VI. <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was agreed to hold the next meeting of the Council at 11 a.m. on Thursday,
                    20th June.</p>
